 at the Crystal Palace Exhibition |jstor=24191006 |journal=Journal of Glass Studies |publisher=Corning Museum of Glass |volume=42 |pages=133\u2013143 |issn=0075-4250 }}\n* {{cite journal |last=Young |first=Paul |year=2007 |title=\"Carbon, Mere Carbon\": The Kohinoor, the Crystal Palace, and the Mission to Make Sense of British India |url= |journal=Nineteenth-Century Contexts |volume=29 |issue=4 |pages=343\u2013358 |doi=10.1080/08905490701768089 }}\n* {{cite book|first1=Sir George|last1=Younghusband|first2=Cyril|last2=Davenport|title=The Crown Jewels of England|url=https://archive.org/details/TheCrownJewelsOfEngland|year=1919|publisher=Cassell & Co.|asin=B00086FM86}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Koh-i-Noor Diamond}}\n* {{Wikisource-inline|links=[[s:The Folk-Lore Journal/Volume 4/A Story of the Koh-i-N\u00fbr|the Koh-i-Noor]]}}\n\n{{Crown Jewels of the United Kingdom}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Koh-I-Noor}}\n[[Category:Crown Jewels of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Jewels of the Mughal Empire]]\n[[Category:Diamonds originating in India]]\n[[Category:History of India]]\n[[Category:History of Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Sikh Empire]]\n[[Category:1739 in Asia]]\n[[Category:Persian words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Golconda diamonds]]\n", "name_user": "110.44.121.11", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koh-i-Noor"}
{"title_page": "Maejor discography", "text_new": "{{For|production work by Maejor|Maejor production discography}}\n{{More citations needed|date=November 2013}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist       = [[Maejor]]\n|Image        = Maejor Ali.png\n|Caption      = Maejor in 2014.\n|Studio       = \n|EP           = 2\n|Compilation  = \n|Singles      = 11\n|Soundtrack   = \n|Music videos = 20\n|B-sides      =\n|1Option      = 4\n|1Option name = Mixtapes\n}}\n\nThe '''discography of [[Maejor]]''', formerly known as '''Bei Maejor''' and later '''Maejor Ali''', an American [[hip hop music|hip hop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] [[music producer]] and [[singer-songwriter]], consists of two [[extended play]]s (EPs), four [[mixtapes]], 15 [[Single (music)|singles]] (including three as a [[Featuring|featured artist]]) and 20 [[music videos]].\n\n== EPs ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays, with selected details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Upscale''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2012/03/29/new-music-bei-maejor-upscale-ep/|title=New Music: Bei Maejor \u2013 'Upscale' [EP]|work=rap-up.com|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: March 29, 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hiphop-n-more.com/2012/03/bei-maejor-upscale-ep/|title=Bei Maejor \u2013 \u2018Upscale\u2019 (EP) - HipHop-N-More|date=29 March 2012|work=hiphop-n-more.com|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref>\n* Label: [[Self-released]]\n* Formats: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Spirit''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.datpiff.com/Maejor-Ali-Spirit-EP-mixtape.662478.html|title=Maejor Ali - Spirit EP Hosted by DJ Carisma|work=datpiff.com|accessdate=5 April 2017}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: November 1, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/maejor-ali-spirit-ep-hosted-by-dj-carisma-new-mixtape.115543.html|title=Maejor - Spirit EP